parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, making it difficult or impossible to drive at night, which can lead to accidents or other safety hazards.
symptoms: yellowing or hazing of the headlight lenses
reflective coating inside the headlight housing burns off
inability to see more than 15 feet in front of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket can cause the engine to overheat, leading to costly repairs, engine damage, and potential safety risks, such as stalling or loss of control while driving.
symptoms: white smoke emits from the tailpipe

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine mounts can cause the engine to rise and become unsecure, leading to potential safety risks, such as loss of control while driving, and damage to other engine components.
symptoms: causing the engine to rise and become unsecure
and leading to rear brake and rotor failures

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various components to malfunction, leading to safety risks, such as loss of lighting, inability to sound the horn, and stalling, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: vehicle catches fire under the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or continue running uncontrollably, leading to safety risks, such as accidents or fires.
symptoms: Ignition switch spins in a circular motion
vehicle continues to run after key is removed

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to safety risks, such as accidents or injuries.
symptoms: vehicle catches fire near the master cylinder reservoir.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to safety risks, such as accidents or injuries.
symptoms: vehicle changes RPMs for no reason
cruise control increases/decreases speed on its own.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the horn system can cause the vehicle to be unable to sound the horn, leading to safety risks, such as accidents or injuries.
symptoms: design of the horn location changes as the wheel turns
making it difficult to sound the horn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the theft alarm system can cause the alarm to go off randomly, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: battery needs to be disconnected to shut it off.
